    Note the registry search list is set to include music, otherwise grouping would not be found above. In a group tag, the path block tag (jpop in this case) is located, looking first in every registry on the search list and if not found then in  the current registry. If the path block is not found and it specifies a regular expression or * then every entry in the current registry, if set, is matched against.
